SOP: Hydraulic System Pressure Loss, Fluid Contamination, and Pump Cavitation

1. Notify the area supervisor and control room operator immediately.
2. Monitor hydraulic pressure, pump temperature, and filter differential pressure via SCADA.
3. If pressure drops below 120 bar or temperature exceeds 70 C, initiate a controlled shutdown.
4. Perform Lockout/Tagout (LOTO) on the main pump motor and isolate accumulator pressure.
5. Inspect the system for visible external leaks, burst hoses, and failing fittings.
6. Verify reservoir fluid level and inspect for fluid foaming or cloudiness (water ingress).
7. Check the indicator on the return-line filter; replace filter element if differential pressure exceeds 2.5 bar.
8. If pump cavitation is suspected (high-pitched whining), inspect suction line strainer and pump coupling.
9. Collect fluid sample for particle count analysis (ISO 4406) and water content testing.
10. Restore system, bleed air from high points, re-pressurize accumulators, and verify pressure stability before restarting.
